Map Model Variables

Define the mapping between variables in the model to fields in the Salesforce object or to columns in the supplemental dataset.

If you want to include external data or computed fields in queries associated with this model, click Add Supplemental Dataset and fill in the following fields.

Connected Salesforce Object	Name of the selected Salesforce object. Read only.
Connected Salesforce Object ID Field	

Name of the Object ID field in the selected Salesforce object. Einstein automatically selects a default field. If you want to change this setting, click the x and select a different field.

Supplemental Dataset	

Name of the supplemental dataset that contains the additional data to use when scoring records.

Model Variable	Name of the variable in the model.
Object Field	Name of the field in the Salesforce object.
Dataset Column	Name of the corresponding column in the supplemental dataset, if applicable.

If you want to deploy this model using automated prediction fields, you must map all fields. If you don't need to map all fields or use this model for the prediction Transformation, then you can skip mapping fields.

If the model is configured with a projected prediction, be sure to map the projected prediction variable, and map the Record ID variable to the unique identifier column in the trending dataset.

To learn more, see Configure Projected Predictions.
title: Mapping Model Variables in Einstein Discovery
